    {
      "para_id": "p7",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "Response to the European Commission’s public consultation for the Digital Fairness Act"
      ],
      "ordinal": 7,
      "text": "Bits of Freedom is a Dutch digital rights organization. For over two decades it has been our mission to shape the internet in support of an open and just society. We welcome the Commission’s ambition to ensure fairness for consumers online.",
      "char_len": 240,
      "chunk_word_count": 42,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.98,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8333333333333334
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.8933333333333333,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p8",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "Response to the European Commission’s public consultation for the Digital Fairness Act"
      ],
      "ordinal": 8,
      "text": "Through techniques like addictive design and personalization, large online platforms impede consumers’ freedom to organize their online environment and time as they wish. As a result, people spend more time online than they would like and make “choices” they would not otherwise make, as stated in the European Commissions Study to support the Fitness Check of EU consumer law. End users of online platforms have limited autonomy. Many of the misleading practices enabling this, are not yet sufficiently regulated. The Digital Fairness Act is the perfect opportunity to address these issues.",
      "char_len": 591,
      "chunk_word_count": 91,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9760479041916168,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8477157360406091
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9820359281437127,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p9",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "Recommendations: users in the lead"
      ],
      "ordinal": 9,
      "text": "Bits of Freedom believes that people should be able to make autonomous and conscious choices online. The Digital Fairness Act can ensure this by imposing measures on techniques that attract attention and retain attention. By legally restricting the use of manipulative design techniques, a fairer digital environment can be created. With the right rules in place, users will no longer be dependent on the choices made for them by large platforms, but will regain control over their own online lives.",
      "char_len": 499,
      "chunk_word_count": 80,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9833333333333333,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8416833667334669
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9875,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p10",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "Recommendations: users in the lead"
      ],
      "ordinal": 10,
      "text": "To maximize its impact, the Digital Fairness Act should regulate the ‘user journey’ from start to finish. The process leading to a loss of autonomy for the end user begins even before a person opens an app (when their attention is attracted) and continues as the person uses an app (their attention is retained).",
      "char_len": 312,
      "chunk_word_count": 54,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9652509652509652,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8301282051282052
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9739382239382239,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p11",
      "section_id": "s3",
      "section_path": [
        "A. Attracting attention"
      ],
      "ordinal": 11,
      "text": "Many platforms are designed to attract users’ attention. Frequent notifications and psychological tricks that play on the fear of missing out, cause people to lose control over whether, when and how they use these platforms.",
      "char_len": 224,
      "chunk_word_count": 35,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9736842105263158,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8482142857142857
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.7816520467836259,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p12",
      "section_id": "s3",
      "section_path": [
        "A. Attracting attention"
      ],
      "ordinal": 12,
      "text": "Consumers should have the right not to be disturbed. Regulating attention attracting practices can help users regain control over whether and when they open a platform. Bits of Freedom",
      "char_len": 184,
      "chunk_word_count": 29,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9871794871794872,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8478260869565217
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.7001068376068377,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p13",
      "section_id": "s3",
      "section_path": [
        "A. Attracting attention"
      ],
      "ordinal": 13,
      "text": "Pagina: 2/3",
      "char_len": 11,
      "chunk_word_count": 3,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.6,
        "digit": 0.2,
        "non_space": 0.9090909090909091
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.14999999999999997,
        "flags": [
          "very_short"
        ]
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p14",
      "section_id": "s3",
      "section_path": [
        "A. Attracting attention"
      ],
      "ordinal": 14,
      "text": "advises the European Commission to take the following measures.",
      "char_len": 63,
      "chunk_word_count": 9,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9818181818181818,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.873015873015873
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.4363636363636364,
        "flags": [
          "very_short"
        ]
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p15",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "A. Attracting attention",
        "1. Give users control over notifications"
      ],
      "ordinal": 15,
      "text": "Notifications should be disabled by default;",
      "char_len": 44,
      "chunk_word_count": 6,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9743589743589743,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8863636363636364
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.43076923076923074,
        "flags": [
          "very_short"
        ]
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p16",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "A. Attracting attention",
        "1. Give users control over notifications"
      ],
      "ordinal": 16,
      "text": "Users should be able to indicate per category which notifications they do or do not want to receive (e.g. for personal messages, but not for friend requests);",
      "char_len": 158,
      "chunk_word_count": 28,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9545454545454546,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8354430379746836
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.6603535353535355,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p17",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "A. Attracting attention",
        "1. Give users control over notifications"
      ],
      "ordinal": 17,
      "text": "A distinction must be made between notifications from other users (comments) and notifications generated by the platform itself (“you may be interested in this”), as well as between badge notifications (in the app environment) and push notifications (outside the app environment).",
      "char_len": 280,
      "chunk_word_count": 41,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.95,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8571428571428571
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.8555555555555556,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p18",
      "section_id": "s5",
      "section_path": [
        "A. Attracting attention",
        "2. Enable users to manage reward systems"
      ],
      "ordinal": 18,
      "text": "Reward systems that encourage repeated use at fixed times, such as rewarding “streaks”, should be disabled by default. If users choose not to be exposed to such reward systems, that should not entail the loss of other functionalities.",
      "char_len": 234,
      "chunk_word_count": 38,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9644670050761421,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8418803418803419
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.8205724760293289,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p19",
      "section_id": "s6",
      "section_path": [
        "A. Attracting attention",
        "B. Retaining attention"
      ],
      "ordinal": 19,
      "text": "As soon as a user opens a platform, platforms employ a combination of profiling and manipulative design to keep that person online for as long as possible. As a result, people often spend more time and attention on a platform than they intended.",
      "char_len": 245,
      "chunk_word_count": 43,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9802955665024631,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8285714285714286
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9088327859879585,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p20",
      "section_id": "s6",
      "section_path": [
        "A. Attracting attention",
        "B. Retaining attention"
      ],
      "ordinal": 20,
      "text": "Consumers should have the right to be protected against unfair practices. Regulating attention-retention practices can help users regain control over how much time they spend online and what they spend that time doing.",
      "char_len": 218,
      "chunk_word_count": 33,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9838709677419355,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8532110091743119
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.758736559139785,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p21",
      "section_id": "s7",
      "section_path": [
        "A. Attracting attention",
        "3. Prohibit harmful design"
      ],
      "ordinal": 21,
      "text": "To increase the amount of time people spend on a platform, platforms detach users from reality: users lose their sense of time and are tempted to keep scrolling, watching or clicking. This approach is reminiscent of casinos, where the lack of windows and the tempting lights of slot machines keep people inside for hours, far away from the outside world. Bits of Freedom advises the European Commission to take the following measures.",
      "char_len": 434,
      "chunk_word_count": 72,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.977961432506887,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.836405529953917
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9834710743801653,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p22",
      "section_id": "s7",
      "section_path": [
        "A. Attracting attention",
        "3. Prohibit harmful design"
      ],
      "ordinal": 22,
      "text": "Design elements that retain consumers’ attention should be prohibited, including a ban on the endless scroll function, and a ban on auto-playing videos, including previews;",
      "char_len": 172,
      "chunk_word_count": 25,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9594594594594594,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8604651162790697
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.6182057057057058,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p23",
      "section_id": "s7",
      "section_path": [
        "A. Attracting attention",
        "3. Prohibit harmful design"
      ],
      "ordinal": 23,
      "text": "Users must be given the possibility to monitor how much time they spend on the platform during their active session through a visible time indicator. Users should be able to turn this feature on and off.",
      "char_len": 203,
      "chunk_word_count": 36,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9880952380952381,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8275862068965517
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.8077380952380953,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p24",
      "section_id": "s8",
      "section_path": [
        "A. Attracting attention",
        "4. Give users more control over sorting algorithms"
      ],
      "ordinal": 24,
      "text": "Platforms use recommendation algorithms to keep users engaged for as long as possible. These algorithms determine what content users see and in what order. Recommendation algorithms often offer content that elicits",
      "char_len": 214,
      "chunk_word_count": 31,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9891304347826086,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8598130841121495
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.7321256038647344,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p25",
      "section_id": "s8",
      "section_path": [
        "A. Attracting attention",
        "4. Give users more control over sorting algorithms"
      ],
      "ordinal": 25,
      "text": "Pagina: 3/3",
      "char_len": 11,
      "chunk_word_count": 3,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.6,
        "digit": 0.2,
        "non_space": 0.9090909090909091
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.14999999999999997,
        "flags": [
          "very_short"
        ]
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p26",
      "section_id": "s8",
      "section_path": [
        "A. Attracting attention",
        "4. Give users more control over sorting algorithms"
      ],
      "ordinal": 26,
      "text": "strong reactions, such as polarising or extreme messages, rather than nuanced content. As a result, users spend more time on the platform than they intended. Bits of Freedom advises the European Commission to take the following measures.",
      "char_len": 237,
      "chunk_word_count": 37,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9701492537313433,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8481012658227848
      },
