      "section_path": [
        "A. Attracting attention",
        "4. Give users more control over sorting algorithms"
      ],
      "ordinal": 28,
      "text": "When creating an account, platforms should offer users a menu with different types of sorting algorithms, such as chronological order or algorithms based on specific topics or focused on specific regions. These algorithms should be easy to find, clearly explained, and it should be possible to set them as default.",
      "char_len": 314,
      "chunk_word_count": 50,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9773584905660377,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8439490445859873
